{
  "local_port": 38298,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the places to visit in Chennai?",
  "response": "Chennai, the bustling capital of Tamil Nadu, offers a diverse range of attractions for tourists. Here are some top places to visit in Chennai:\n\n1. **Marina Beach**:\n   - One of the longest urban beaches in the world, Marina Beach is a must-visit. Enjoy the sea breeze, try local street food, and watch the sunset.\n\n2. **Kapaleeshwarar Temple**:\n   - This ancient temple dedicated to Lord Shiva is a fine example of Dravidian architecture. It's located in Mylapore and is a serene place to visit.\n\n3. **Fort St. George**:\n   - Built in 1644, this fort houses the Tamil Nadu Legislative Assembly and the Secretariat. The Fort Museum inside showcases artifacts from the colonial era.\n\n4. **Government Museum**:\n   - Located in Egmore, this museum is one of the oldest in India. It has an extensive collection of antiques, including art, archaeology, and natural history.\n\n5. **Valluvar Kottam**:\n   - A monument dedicated to the Tamil poet-saint Valluvar, this architectural marvel is built to resemble a temple chariot.\n\n6. **San Thome Basilica**:\n   - A Roman Catholic minor basilica, believed to house the tomb of St. Thomas the Apostle. The neo-Gothic style of the church is worth admiring.\n\n7. **Birla Planetarium**:\n   - Located near the central railway station, this planetarium offers educational shows about space and astronomy.\n\n8. **DakshinaChitra**:\n   - An open-air museum that showcases the art, architecture, and lifestyle of South India. It\u2019s a great place to learn about the region\u2019s rich cultural heritage.\n\n9. **Guindy National Park**:\n   - One of the smallest national parks in India, it\u2019s home to a variety of flora and fauna. The park also includes a snake park and a children's park.\n\n10. **Arignar Anna Zoological Park (Vandalur Zoo)**:\n    - Located about 30 kilometers from Chennai, this zoo is one of the largest in South Asia and houses a wide range of animals and birds.\n\n11. **ISKCON Temple**:\n    - Known for its stunning architecture and serene atmosphere, the ISKCON Temple is a great place for spiritual seekers and also offers delicious vegetarian food.\n\n12. **Ashtalakshmi Temple**:\n    - A relatively new temple, it\u2019s dedicated to the eight forms of Goddess Lakshmi. The temple\u2019s architecture and seaside location make it a popular spot.\n\nThese attractions offer a blend of history, culture, nature, and modernity, making Chennai a fascinating city to explore.",
